<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1858,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ravenna" authorityYear="1988" box="[136,417,1859,1884]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Trimezia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="281" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="portosecurensis">
<emphasis box="[136,417,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">Trimezia portosecurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ravenna, P." box="[626,808,1859,1885]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref4828" refString="Ravenna, P. (1988) New species and miscellaneous notes in the genus Trimezia (Iridaceae) - II. Onira Botanical Leaflets 1: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1988">Ravenna (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, who cited 
<emphasis box="[938,1127,1859,1885]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">T S. Santos 1954</emphasis>
(Herbarium Ravenna) as the 
<typeStatus box="[136,237,1894,1920]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">holotype</typeStatus>
, which is considered non-existent following the current accepted custom with respect to treatment of type specimens of the Herbarium Ravenna (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Deble, L. P. &amp; Alves, F. S." box="[647,900,1930,1957]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281" pagination="20 - 26" refId="ref3720" refString="Deble, L. P. &amp; Alves, F. S. (2017 a) The type of Cypella herbertii subsp. brevicristata Ravenna (Iridaceae: Tigridieae). Balduinia 56: 20 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.5902 / 2358198026217" type="journal article" year="2017">Deble &amp; Alves 2017a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Deble, L. P. &amp; Alves, F. S." box="[915,988,1930,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281" pagination="41" refId="ref3769" refString="Deble, L. P. &amp; Alves, F. S. (2017 b) Taxonomic novelties for the genus Cypella (Iridaceae): new species, synonymies and nomenclatural types. Kew Bulletin 72: 41. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 017 - 9708 - 3" type="journal article" year="2017">
2017 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil, A. S. B. &amp; Hall, C. F. &amp; Bittrich, V. &amp; Amaral, M. C. E." box="[974,988,1930,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281" pagination="144 - 155" refId="ref4205" refString="Gil, A. S. B., Hall, C. F., Bittrich, V. &amp; Amaral, M. C. E. (2019) A new species, new synonyms, typifications, and a name correction in Neomarica from Brazil (Trimezieae, Iridaceae). Brittonia 71: 144 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12228 - 018 - 9563 - z" type="journal article" year="2019">b</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, Gil 
<emphasis box="[1048,1108,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">et al.</emphasis>
2019). The isotype consulted at CEPEC has a preserved flower and thus it is chosen here as the 
<typeStatus box="[895,998,1966,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[1014,1082,1966,1993]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1744,1766]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,190,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[195,1392,190,1720]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lectotype (designated here) of Neomarica portosecurensis. Reflora - Herbário Virtual.Available from: http://reflora.jbrj.gov. br/reflora/herbarioVirtual/ConsultaPublicoHVUC/ConsultaPublicoHVUC.do?idTestemunho=4555772.Accessed: 27 Oct 2020." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5755566" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5755566/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) (Art. 9.3 &amp; 9.12, 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." pageId="6" pageNumber="281" refId="ref5008" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[1394,1452,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="281">et al.</emphasis>
2018
